import java.text.DecimalFormat;

double/float number=0.999999999;
DecimalFormat df = new DecimalFormat("#.00")/("0.0000")->agr decimal se aage bhi zero chaiye toh decimal se aage zero lga denge;
System.out.println(df.format(number));

output->0.99
                                    OR
                                   
double/float n=4;                                   
System.out.printf("\n%.4f",n/3);->point lgana jaruri hai % k baad jbhi ye kaam krega

output->1.3333

note-> 1. second wala ek baar hi use kr skte hai kyuki ye line change nhi krta or agr line change krani hai toh %d se aage \n lgana pdhega.
2.Agr \n nhi lgaya dusri line m toh jo dusri line print hoegi vo first line k sath hi aajaegi jisse first wali line bhi shi se print nhi hogi. 
